
   LATEST NEWS   12.4.90   

No real news today, just thought I'd
keep you up to date with the instalation
of the direct lines into the mainframe
at Camden.

BT have now dug up the garden to put the
lines into the basement. (At least we
HOPE that's why they dug up the garden).

Did you know BT engineers don't work on
the Thursday before Easter because it's
Maundy Thursday and BT USED to be a
Nationalised company!?!

Maybe BT could use up some of that 7
million pound a DAY profit by letting us
have cheap calls on Maundy Thursday ? 
According to Ceefax, BT are not even
giving us the usual cheap rate calls
over Easter.

